      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change less than 5% between successive refinements, with reported GCI.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw-rod construct model. Stiffness QoI changed by 1.8% between medium and fine meshes; GCI = 2.3%. Final mesh uses 187,000 quadratic tetrahedral elements. Discretization error is well-controlled; achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals must converge below 1e-6 for all load steps; contact penetration tolerance documented.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear load steps converged with force residual below 1e-7. Augmented Lagrangian contact with penetration tolerance 0.001 mm. No divergence events observed across 11-specimen ensemble. Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with independent peer review of model setup; checklist-based QA review prior to result submission.",
      "rationale": "Model setup followed a documented simulation workflow (SOP-FEA-2022-07). An independent engineer performed peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions. Pre-submission checklist completed and archived. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection (linear elastic with nonlinear contact) must be justified by literature evidence and sensitivity analysis demonstrating plasticity effects are negligible below yield.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model with Ti-6Al-4V properties (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34) is justified by the sub-yield loading regime for stiffness QoI. Sensitivity analysis showed less than 2% difference in stiffness when elasto-plastic model used. Literature (Patel et al. 2010) supports linear elastic assumption for pre-yield F1717 constructs. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to certified material certificates and CMM measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties sourced from certified mill certificates (mean E=114.2 GPa, CV=1.1%). Screw geometry from CMM measurements with tolerances ±0.01 mm. Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainty (1000 samples) contributed 1.9% to QoI uncertainty budget. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be production-representative with documented lot traceability; N≥10 specimens required.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested, sourced from two production lots with full traceability documentation. Specimens are production-representative per DePuy Synthes quality records. Sample size meets the N≥10 acceptance criterion. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate in vivo loading environment across multiple load cases; at minimum, compression-bending at two offset distances required.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single anterior offset of 40 mm per ASTM F1717 protocol. While this represents the standard regulatory test condition, only one offset distance was evaluated. The required level 3 demands multi-condition testing; achieved level 2 reflects the single-condition limitation. This shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory gold standard for this device class."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions must demonstrably replicate experimental fixture constraints; documented mapping between test setup and model boundary conditions required.",
      "rationale": "Experimental fixture constraints (fixed base, actuator load application point) mapped directly to FEA boundary conditions with documented correspondence table. Actuator load application replicated as a rigid body constraint on the superior rod end. Equivalency confirmed by independent review. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percent difference < 10% for all specimens.",
      "rationale": "All three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% across all 11 specimens. Stiffness: E/uval=1.21; Yield force: E/uval=1.54; Force at 40 mm: E/uval=1.33. Output comparison is fully quantified and meets the acceptance criterion. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must be directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory acceptance criteria for pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs are directly linked to the clinically relevant failure mode of construct bending fatigue and acute overload. Achieved level 3 exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "The relevance of the validation activities to the COU is considered self-evident given that the validation experiment is the ASTM F1717 protocol itself, which is identical in geometry, loading, and fixturing to the intended use scenario. Because the validation domain and the COU domain are, by construction, the same physical test, a formal relevance assessment was judged unnecessary by the modeling team. No separate relevance scoring was performed, and no requiredLevel or achievedLevel has been assigned for this factor.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not established; factor deemed inapplicable by the assessment team on the basis that the COU and validation activity are co-extensive."
    }
